~ two inline marks, only two

This is _italic_ and this is *bold*.

The keeper called the lens a _miracle of glass_, though it was *only* polished stone in a brass cage.

~ punctuation inside prose cannot trigger a mark by accident,
~ because the marks wrap a token rather than living at the start of a line

I multiplied 5*6*7 and the 6 stays plain.

A sentence beginning "1970. It was a cold winter." stays a sentence.

A line beginning "> half of them never wrote back" stays a line.
